## Your Job
 
For **backend/data/API work**: follow `references/task-list.md` in order.
After each task, run tests and confirm they pass before moving on.
 
For **frontend UI work**: read `references/ui-design.md` first, then
`references/frontend-guide.md`. The UI guide takes precedence on all
visual and component decisions.
 
Read `references/akshare-guide.md` before touching any data layer code.
Read `references/api-guide.md` before touching `api/app.py`.
 
---
 
## Hard Rules
 
- **Never recreate QSW code.** The words `quantum_walk`, `QuantumStochasticWalk`,
  `graph_builder`, `evolution_dynamics`, `braket`, `QSWConfig` must not appear
  in any new file.
- **Never use yfinance.** Every call to `yf.download`, `yf.Ticker`, or
  `import yfinance` must be removed and replaced with AKShare equivalents.
- **Never use QSW parameters in the frontend.** `omega`, `evolution_time`,
  `evolution_method` must not appear in any new or updated UI code.
- **Keep the API response shape.** The frontend depends on `qsw_result`,
  `holdings`, `benchmarks`, `sector_allocation`, `risk_metrics`, `stage_info`.
  Do not rename or remove these keys.
- **Keep `frontend/src/services/api.js` endpoint URLs unchanged** unless the
  backend route itself changes.
- **Run tests after every file change.** Use `pytest tests/ -x -q` for backend,
  `npm run build` for frontend.
- **One file at a time.** Make a change, verify, commit, move on.
- **Do not touch `notebooks/`.** They are reference only.
 
---
 
